  "text": "Recent work has shown that CTRP9 hormone plays a protective role in the heart against ischemia/reperfusion injury [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , as well as attenuating neointima formation in response to vascular injury [CITATION_3] . However, the potential protective function and mechanism of action of CTRP9 in the context of dietinduced obesity and Type 2 diabetes remain unknown. Here, we provide in vivo and in vitro evidence that CTRP9 is, indeed, a novel adipokine with important metabolic functions.",
